<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-06-07T20:10:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-06-07T20:10:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                        <head>199. Telegram From the Joint Chiefs of Staff to the Commander in
                            Chief, European Command (<persName corresp="#p_LGLL1" type="to">Lemnitzer</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d199fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> Library,
                                National Security File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                                Histories, Middle East Crisis, Vol. 7, Appendix H. Top Secret;
                                Immediate. Repeated Immediate to <gloss target="#t_CNO1">CNO</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CINCLANT1">CINCLANT</gloss>,
                                CINCLANTFLT, <gloss target="#t_CINCUSNAVEUR1">CINCUSNAVEUR</gloss>,
                                    <gloss target="#t_COMSIXTHFLT1">COMSIXTHFLT</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CTF1">CTF</gloss> 64, <gloss target="#t_USS1">USS</gloss> LIBERTY, <gloss target="#t_HQ1">HQ</gloss>-NSAEUR,
                                NSAEUR OFF GERMANY, DIRNSA, DIRNAVSECGRU, ADIRNAVSECGRU,
                                DIRNAVSECGRULANT, DIRNAVSECGRUEUR.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1967-06-08T01:10:00+00:00">June 8, 1967,
                                0110Z</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>7347. Subj: <gloss target="#t_USS1">USS</gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">Liberty</hi> (<gloss target="#t_U1">U</gloss>).</p>
                        <p>Refs: a. <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 7337/072230Z Jun 67;<note n="2" xml:id="d199fn2">
                                <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> telegram 7337 to USCINCEUR,
                                072230Z Jun 67, modified the instructions in <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 6724 (<ref target="#d118">Document 118</ref>) to
                                provide that the <hi rend="italic">Liberty</hi> should approach no
                                closer than 20 NM to the <gloss target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss> and 15
                                NM to Israel. (<persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName>
                                Library, National Security File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                                Histories, Middle East Crisis, Vol. 7, Appendix H)</note> b. <gloss target="#t_COMSIXTHFLT1">COMSIXTHFLT</gloss> 071503Z Jun 67
                                (Notal).<note n="3" xml:id="d199fn3">
                                <ref target="#d192">Document 192</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>(<gloss target="#t_U1">U</gloss>) Cancel ref a.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>(TS) Reg <hi rend="italic">Liberty</hi> comply new op areas
                                defined last sentence para 2 ref b, until further notice, i.e., not
                                closer than 100 NM to Israel, Syria, Egypt and 25 NM to Cyprus.<note n="4" xml:id="d199fn4">The <gloss target="#t_USS1">U.S.S.</gloss>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Liberty</hi> did not receive this message. See
                                        <ref target="#d217">Document 217</ref>.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>